obliterate = Destroy utterly; wipe out
abbreviate = Shorten (a word, phrase, or text)
mendacious = Not telling the truth; lying
plunder = Steal goods from (a place or person), typically using force and in a time of war or civil disorder
rapacious = Aggressively greedy or ravenous; plundering
blasphemy = The action or offence of speaking sacrilegiously about God or sacred things; profane talk
ravenous = Extremely hungry
perspicacious = Having strong insight into and understanding of things
frenetic = Fast and energetic in a rather wild and uncontrolled way
myopic = Lack of discernment or long-range perspective in thinking or planning: “… thinking.”
myopia = Illness; distant objects appear blurred
